text: Ten Wood is a 17.7 hectare biological Site of Special Scientific Interest east of Burrough Green in Cambridgeshire. This ancient wood is of the ash/maple type, which has a high conservation value as it has a restricted and declining distribution. Other trees include hazel and pedunculate oak. There is also a population of the rare oxlip. The site is private land with no public access. ==References== Category:Sites of Special Scientific Interest in Cambridgeshire
